urls.description: James Brown shared a post on Instagram: "Time Out rates Huddersfield railway station as the 7th most beautiful in the world. I like the Harold Wilson statue in front of it. The first thing you see when you walk out of the station is a massive lion on top of the building opposite. Apparently the original stone one fell off at some point and nearly killed someone below. Lion kills man in Pennines would have been an eye catching headline. I was up there working with @adamgstudio and @peterotooleart on a project I’m bringing out next year. Huddersfield is a nice Pennine town. I don’t think I’ve ever been before but I had great healthy breakfasts in the Arcade Cafe, lunch in the brilliant modernist Bath House turned Toast cafe at the Barbara Hepworth building at Huddersfield Uni and mainly just got to play out with Adam and Pete in their massive old stone mill based studio. Stan up comedian @neilsummers_ popped in to see us and we had a good time. It was nice to be in an office again having
